#### Naming styles ####

# CODING STANDARDS - Magic Strings/Numbers
# NOTE: .editorconfig cannot enforce this automatically. 
# Consider adding SonarAnalyzer.CSharp or Roslynator NuGet packages for automated detection.
#
# PRINCIPLE: Avoid "magic strings" - hardcoded string literals with semantic meaning
# BAD:  if (assemblyName.Contains("Application")) 
# GOOD: if (assemblyName.Contains(LayerNames.Application))
#
# WHEN TO EXTRACT TO CONSTANTS:
# - Assembly/namespace names used for conventions ("Application", "Infrastructure.Data")
# - File paths, URLs, connection string keys
# - Configuration keys, setting names
# - Status codes, error codes, enum-like strings
# - Any string used in multiple places
#
# WHEN LITERALS ARE ACCEPTABLE:
# - One-off log messages (unless repeated)
# - Test data strings
# - Display text (should eventually be in resources for i18n)
# - Exception messages (debatable - consider resource files)
#
# RECOMMENDATION: 
# 1. Create constants classes per domain/layer (e.g., LayerConventions.cs, ConfigurationKeys.cs)
# 2. Add SonarAnalyzer.CSharp NuGet package for S1075 (hardcoded URIs), S1185, etc.
# 3. Review code for repeated strings and extract to constants

